  "plainText": "Dreadstone\nObject Info\n40\nSource\nDropped by\nCrafting\nDescription\nTransmute Pure Horror into Dreadstone.\n×3 ( only)\nFilters\n(for ).\nMiscellaneous\n\"dreadstone\"\nExclusive to:\n“It seems to reflect shadows instead of light.”\n–Wilson\n“Eww, why does this rock feel so cold and clammy?”\n–Willow\n“Is just rock, not scary! ...Right?”\n–Wolfgang\n“It is cold... and beautiful.”\n–Wendy\n“IT IS HARD, COLD, AND EVIL. I LOVE IT”\n–WX-78\n“Metamorphic, if I'm not mistaken.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“There's something off aboot it.”\n–Woodie\n“Petrified nightmares.”\n–Maxwell\n“A stöne öf ill ömen.”\n–Wigfrid\n“We're not sure if we like that rock.”\n–Webber\n“Terrible and beautiful all at once.”\n–Warly\n“Pretty”\n–Wormwood\n“It's evil-lookin', but tough as nails.”\n–Winona\n“A stone as black as night.”\n–Wortox\n“Pretty rocks!”\n–Wurt\n“It's just a rock, what's so scary about a rock?”\n–Walter\n“As off-putting as it is, it could be useful.”\n–Wanda\nDreadstone is an item exclusive to Don't Starve Together. Dreadstone is primarily obtained by destroying the Cracked Pillars that bind the Nightmare Werepig. After mining away the outer Marble layer, the pillars are indestructible and can only be destroyed by the Nightmare Werepig's slam attack, which it only uses after losing enough HP. The Dreadstone can also be mined from Dreadstone Outcrop.\nWith the Shadow Courtier skill, Wilson can transmute 3 Pure Horrors into 1 Dreadstone, as well as transmute 1 Dreadstone back into 2 Pure Horrors.\nAlong with Pure Horror, Dreadstone is used to craft Dreadstone Helm, Dreadstone Armor and Dreadstone Wall. 5 Dreadstones can be offered to the Beckoning Hand after defeating the Ancient Fuelweaver to summon Charlie and permanently activate the Shadow Rift.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×6\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×5\n×5\n×3\n×3\n×2\n×5\n×4\n×2\n×5\n×8\n×5\n×8\n×2\n×20\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nBeta Dreadstone Icon\nBeta Dreadstone\nView or edit this template\nDon't 