  "wikitext": "{{Object Infobox\n|craft_desctiption = ''Transmute Pure Horror into Dreadstone.''\n|image=Dreadstone Dropped.png\n|icon=Dreadstone.png\n|ingredient1=Pure Horror\n|multiplier1=3 ({{Pic|28|Wilson Portrait|Wilson}} only)\n|filter={{Pic32|Wilson Filter}}\n|stack=40\n|spawnCode=\"dreadstone\"\n|droppedBy={{Pic32|Cracked Pillar Map Icon|Cracked Pillar}}{{Pic32|Dreadstone Outcrop}}{{Pic32|Mega Blight}}\n|skill = Shadow Courtier\n|skillOwner = Wilson\n}}\n\n{{Exclusivity||Don't Starve Together}}\n\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = It seems to reflect shadows instead of light.\n|willow = Eww, why does this rock feel so cold and clammy?\n|wolfgang = Is just rock, not scary! ...Right?\n|wendy = It is cold... and beautiful.\n|wx78 = IT IS HARD, COLD, AND EVIL. I LOVE IT\n|wickerbottom = Metamorphic, if I'm not mistaken.\n|woodie = There's something off aboot it.\n|maxwell = Petrified nightmares.\n|wigfrid = A stöne öf ill ömen.\n|webber = We're not sure if we like that rock.\n|winona = It's evil-lookin', but tough as nails.\n|warly = Terrible and beautiful all at once.\n|wortox = A stone as black as night.\n|wormwood = Pretty\n|wurt = Pretty rocks!\n|walter = It's just a rock, what's so scary about a rock?\n|wanda = As off-putting as it is, it could be useful.\n|choose = maxwell\n}}\n\n'''Dreadstone''' is an item exclusive to ''[[Don't Starve Together]]''. Dreadstone is primarily obtained by destroying the [[Cracked Pillar]]s that bind the [[Nightmare Werepig]]. After mining away the outer [[Marble]] layer, the pillars are indestructible and can only be destroyed by the Nightmare Werepig's slam attack, which it only uses after losing enough HP. The Dreadstone can also be mined from [[Dreadstone Outcrop]].\n\nWith the [[Shadow Courtier]] skill, [[Wilson]] can transmute 3 Pure Horrors into 1 Dreadstone, as well as transmute 1 Dreadstone back into 2 Pure Horrors.\n\nAlong with [[Pure Horror]], Dreadstone is used to craft [[Dreadstone Helm]], [[Dreadstone Armor]] and [[Dreadstone Wall]]. 5 Dreadstones can be offered to the [[Beckoning Hand]] after defeating the [[Ancient Fuelweaver]] to summon [[Charlie]] and permanently activate the [[Shadow Rift]].\n\n== {{Pic32|Icon Tools}} Usage ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=6\n|result=Dreadstone Armor\n|resultcount=1\n|item2=Pure Horror\n|count2=4\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=4\n|result=Dreadstone Helm\n|resultcount=1\n|item2=Pure Horror\n|count2=4\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=4\n|result=Dreadstone Wall\n|resultcount=4\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=4\n|item2=Boards\n|count2=2\n|result=Dreadstone Pillar Scaffold\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=2\n|item2=Nightmare Fuel\n|count2=5\n|item3=Pure Horror\n|result=Shadowcraft Plinth Kit\n|tool=Ancient Pseudoscience Station\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item2 = Icker Jar\n|count2 = 3\n|item1 = Dreadstone\n|count1 = 5\n|tool = Shadowcraft Plinth\n|result = Icker Preserve Kit\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dreadstone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Possessed Shadow Atrium\n|item4 = Pure Horror\n|item3 = Dark Tatters DST\n|count3 = 2\n|count4 = 5\n|tool = Shadowcraft Plinth\n|result = Shadow Maul}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dreadstone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Possessed Shadow Atrium\n|item3 = Dark Tatters DST\n|count3 = 2\n|item4 = Pure Horror\n|count4 = 5\n|tool = Shadowcraft Plinth\n|result = Beefalo Gloom Bell}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dreadstone\n|count1 = 8\n|item2 = Possessed Shadow Atrium\n|item3 = Dark Tatters DST\n|count3 = 5\n|item4 = Pure Horror\n|count4 = 8\n|tool = Shadowcraft Plinth\n|result = Nightmare Saddle}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1=Dreadstone\n|count1=1\n|result=Pure Horror\n|resultcount=2\n|character = Wilson\n|skill = Shadow Courtier\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dreadstone\n|count1 = 1\n|result = Dread Pebbles\n|resultcount = 20\n|character = Walter\n|skill = Lucky Rounds\n}}\n\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery>\